reasoning_trace:
We are asked to find \(M(v+3w)\). By linearity of matrix multiplication, \(M(v+3w)=Mv+3Mw\). The problem gives \(Mv=\begin{pmatrix}2\\3\end{pmatrix}\) and \(Mw=\begin{pmatrix}-2\\-5\end{pmatrix}\). Compute:
\[
Mv+3Mw=\begin{pmatrix}2\\3\end{pmatrix}+3\begin{pmatrix}-2\\-5\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}2\\3\end{pmatrix}+\begin{pmatrix}-6\\-15\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}2-6\\3-15\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}-4\\-12\end{pmatrix}.
\]
Thus \(M(v+3w)=\begin{pmatrix}-4\\-12\end{pmatrix}\).</think> <answer>\begin{pmatrix}-4\\-12\end{pmatrix}</answer>

