The expression is a finite alternating geometric series with first term \(a = \frac13\) and common ratio \(r = -\frac13\).  
For \(n = 5\) terms, the sum is  

\[
S = a\frac{1-r^{\,n}}{1-r}
   = \frac13\frac{1-(-\frac13)^5}{1-(-\frac13)}
   = \frac13\frac{1+\frac1{243}}{1+\frac13}
   = \frac13\cdot\frac{244/243}{4/3}
   = \frac{244}{972}
   = \frac{61}{243}.
\]

Thus the value of the expression is \(\frac{61}{243}\).
