reasoning_trace:
We recognize the series as a finite geometric series with first term \(a = (2/3)^1\) and common ratio \(r = 2/3\). The sum of the first 10 terms is  

\[
S = a\frac{1-r^{10}}{1-r}
   = \frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{1-(2/3)^{10}}{1-2/3}
   = \frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{1-(2/3)^{10}}{1/3}
   = 2\bigl(1-(2/3)^{10}\bigr).
\]

Compute \((2/3)^{10}=2^{10}/3^{10}=1024/59049\).  

Thus  

\[
S = 2 - 2\cdot\frac{1024}{59049}
   = 2 - \frac{2048}{59049}
   = \frac{2\cdot59049 - 2048}{59049}
   = \frac{118098 - 2048}{59049}
   = \frac{116050}{59049}.
\]

Since 59049 = \(3^{10}\) and the numerator is not divisible by 3, the fraction is already in lowest terms.</think> <answer>\frac{116050}{59049}</answer>

